<b>Cancelling effect - </b>4/17/01 9:43:26 PM<br>~ <b>Sarais</b><blockquote>Just a little side note for some who may not have relized it. You can cancel a songs effect by just left clicking on it.  <br><br>So if your invisible and you make it to the group you want to join safely you don't have to wait 9 seconds for them to see you, just stop singing and left click on the icon and you will appear instantly. <br><br>Just saves a little time and keeps them from turning in circles looking for the person who is talking to them. </blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>You are about to appear!  Oh no! - </b>4/11/01 11:20:26 PM<br>~ <b>Rakina</b><blockquote>Seeing that message can strike fear into you and your group unless you keep this in mind...<br><br>You get the message because for that &quot;tic&quot; you hit a bum note.  Of course this song, like most of our songs, last for three tics withot being refreshed. Since you are playing this song constantly, one of your next two tics will refresh the song effect.  So don't panic unless you get this message three times in a row (how likely is that?)<br><br>You may want to mention this to your group, because unless they are familiar with bard invis, they may freak!<br><br>A couple of other notes about this song.  Lots of people HATE relying on bard invis, why is that?<br><br>1. If any of your group gets to far from you, they're going to become visable in the next 9 seconds.  Now after a while you're going to realise that 6 people travelling within 45 ft of each other is HARD.  Lots of people seem to have skipped mouse-look school, others have lag, or zero sense of direction, get easily distracted,.... The list goes on and on, but for one reason or another I find that in most instances, someone gets sperated from teh rest of the party and causes an incident that makes your whole group wish they'd brought spare undies.<br><br>Tip:  Get all your group members to make a STOP hotkey that says something like '/g STOP!  I've lost you all'  or something like that.  Tell them to use it the instant they have a lag spike, lose sight of the group, or get lost for any other reason (ie. fall in a trap).  If you have track (you will love it when yo do) keep your track window open so that you can quickly click on the person who's lost and track back to them.  <br><br>Oh, and I can not stress how important it is for you to inform the group that it is THEIR responsibilty to keep as close to your booty as possible!</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Welcome to Vistas Un-imagined! - </b>4/11/01 1:45:25 PM<br>~ <b>LeOde</b><blockquote>I gave this song a rating of 1 even though I don't have it memed all the time (the only ones I mem all the time are Selos Accelerando and Selos Consonant Chain). But it's THAT good.<br><br>Once you have this song - the number of things you can do in the game get's bewildering! Suddenly you have access to almost tripple the realestate! All cities become accessible and many more quests... Just about all dungeons before the 30s can be explored safely.<br><br>If you ever get killed - the first thing you should loot is the wind instrument so you can invis yourself immediately (just don't do this near anyone in your group with a pet!).. makes looting much safer! Always keep a spare wind instrument (and Precussion) in the bank so you can handle tricky CR.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Just add. Info - </b>3/25/01 11:27:28 PM<br>~ <b>Iadasi</b><blockquote>I dont have this Song yet BUT ...<br><br>As i play a high lvl necro for in- and sometimes outdoor<br>travelling it is better you have your pet destroyed. You never ever know which way it ll run , which beast it may aggro. The /con thing is right . Under invis if you re not seen every- one cons indifferent. Beasts or NPCs that see through greet you with their normal faction adjusted message ( f.ex. Scowling). Vs. Undeads there is a StandAlone Invis vs Undead Line of spells.<br><br>hope this shines some more light on the invis Thing :-)<br><br>Iadasi <br>Solusek Ro</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
