<b>Very handy group invisibility - </b>1/28/01 2:13:38 PM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>My groups like this song when we are exploring unfamiliar territory like the Mines of Nurga in Frontier Mountains. It is nicer than someone casting Invisibility on you, since they must have that spell memmed, cast it on everyone in the party, and it seems to wear off randomly.<br><br>With this song, your party will be invisible for as long as the song is playing, all immediate and mana-free. Just make sure you stick close together.<br><br>You will see the message &quot;You are starting to appear.&quot; I have found that I never do appear, and have never had this song wear off unless I do something to break it, like sing a different song, or attack a mob.<br><br>Caution: Some things still see through invisibility, especially undead, and many mobs in Kunark and Velious. Just con them, if they are &quot;indifferent&quot;, they cannot see you, its not that they like you. Do not play this song if your casters want to keep their pet. If a pet doesn't see their master, they commit suicide.</blockquote></td></tr></table></blockquote><br><br><br><br>
